# CFRP Bodywork Design & Structural Analysis
## MSc Dissertation — Autonomous Formula Student Race Car (FS-AI 2026)
### University of Hertfordshire | 2025-2026

## Overview
Sole engineer responsible for the complete bodywork 
structural programme for the Hertfordshire Autonomous 
Racing (HAR) Formula Student FS-AI 2026 entry.

## Scope of Work
- Material selection: 2×2 twill woven CFRP face sheets 
  over PVC foam core sandwich panel
- Regulation compliance review against FS-AI rules
- Concept design and weighted decision matrix evaluation
- ANSYS ACP laminate simulation
- VARI manufacturing of physical test specimens
- Physical three-point bending validation
- Test-simulation result correlation

## Key Results
- Three-point bending simulation: 200N load, 200mm span
- Maximum deformation: 4.9×10⁻³ mm
- Shear-dominated core failure mode confirmed
- Physical test results correlated with simulation
- Final bodywork mass: 5-6 kg vs ≤10 kg target

## Tools Used
- ANSYS ACP (Composite PrepPost) — laminate FEA
- ANSYS Mechanical — structural validation
- CATIA V5 & Fusion 360 — concept CAD modelling
- VARI manufacturing process

## Skills Demonstrated
- Composite structural analysis
- Physical test-simulation correlation
- Design for manufacture (composites)
- Engineering documentation and reporting

